<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be a member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[768,930,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Dilaridae" genus="Dilar" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[768,930,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">Dilar hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang" box="[1154,1357,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" refString="Zhang, W., Liu, X. Y., Aspock, U. &amp; Aspock, H. (2015) Revision of Chinese Dilaridae (Insecta: Neuroptera) (Part III): Species of the genus Dilar Rambur from the southern part of mainland China. Zootaxa, 3974 (4), 451 - 494. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.4.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[1234,1291,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1299,1357,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) based on the bifurcated male gonocoxite 
<number box="[556,570,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" value="9.0">9</number>
and the U-shaped gonarcus laterally expanded on both ends. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="Rexavius" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">D. marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[734,863,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Dilaridae" genus="Dilar" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[734,863,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">D. hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the male gonocoxite 
<number box="[1225,1239,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" value="9.0">9</number>
bifurcated into a long spinous and a short unguiform projections. In the other species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1204,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Dilaridae" genus="Dilar" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastatus">
<emphasis box="[1071,1204,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="135">D. hastatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, if the male gonocoxite 
<number box="[282,296,440,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="135" value="9.0">9</number>
is bifurcated, the two projections formed by the bifurcation are almost equal in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
